entries.femaleVariant: Come on, let me show you around.
OK, lead the way.
Rather do this my own way.
Right behind ya.
Rather poke around my own way. You mind?
I have to admit, sometimes I get fed up with all of this.
This is amazing... I'm not used to it being so calm here.
This is where we sleep.
Jeff's office. Control room, storage and flea market crammed into one.
This was my den before the campaign. A place to focus, relax.
Recently, Jeff complained he was a nonstarter because nobody was blackmailing him or out to assassinate him, hah. Kind of a joke.
Politics?
No, of course not. I'll be right behind you, in case.
We can start where Jeff spotted our uninvited guest.
Anything change in here?
Notice anything different in here after the break-in?
No... I don't think so. What do you have in mind?
Mind if I have a look?
Mind if I take a look around?
Be my guest.
We're paying the staffers and for the campaign out of pocket.
Security had to set up somewhere.
What's it like usually?
"Vote for Peralez."
Jeff said he passed out.
Anything seem out of the ordinary? The bedding, its arrangement? Any signs at all?
As if he was dragged back to bed, you mean? No, I didn't notice anything.
So far we've managed to effectively turn down offers to "work with" Night Corp, Biotechnica, Arasaka…
If Jeff can get elected without owing anybody, favors or otherwise – heh, that'd be the real victory.
Blackmail and assassination commonplace in politics?
Too common, I'm afraid.
Should consider yourselves lucky, then, least for now.
entries.maleVariant: You should consider yourselves lucky, then, heh... I mean, at least for now.

entries.femaleVariant: And we keep all the campaign stuff here. It's cheaper that way.
This is where Jeff saw our intruder.
And fired at him, here?
Right after walking out of the bedroom. At least that's how he remembers it.
"So far," you say.
Like any campaign HQ. People shouting, hundreds of calls going on, coming in. My ears are still buzzing…
Doesn't look it anymore…
One of the many small sacrifices I've had to make. This was the first, but it won't be the last.
You're welcome to go up to the roof, if you want. I'll wait here.
Sure thing.
"Vote for Peralez?"
